    <item>
      <title>Archaic Set</title>
      <author>Chalmoro Azohen</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/539090</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/539090#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">5261e41beb72f01a00e01ca69798dd826772a54f</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 30 Oct 2024 03:08:18 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d2bd597616a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d2bd6762967.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d2bd676b703.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/66d41200ce554.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Finally Fixed&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;Thanks to jesco on Discord, I looked back at the textures and found a profound issue. I believe the Warm Greaves have been reading the wrong textures this whole time. All connections should be restored. New BCML and UKMM versions have been uploaded.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bugfix&lt;/em&gt;: Fixed the Archaic Warm Greaves textures&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;From &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/471343"&gt;KB0MB's Tears of the Kingdom mod&lt;/a&gt;, I present the Archaic Tunic, Legwear, and Warm Greaves from Tears of the Kingdom!&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've made a few edits, however.&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;I changed their locations. They're placed in spots reminiscent of their native game: the Archaic Legwear is &lt;span class="Spoiler SelectedElement"&gt;in the Shrine of Resurrection (compared to their position in the Cave of Awakening)&lt;/span&gt;, the Archaic Tunic is &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;by the Ja Baij Shrine (by the combat-related power Shrine, like its position close to the Fuse Shrine)&lt;/span&gt;, and the Archaic Warm Greaves are &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;behind the Mount Hylia waterfall&lt;/span&gt;. I've spoilered the locations for anyone who wants to find them without hints, but feel free to check if you just want to find them easily.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Rauru's arm is built into the Archaic Tunic, something that isn't the case in the original game and KB0MB's mod. Perfect for those who only want it with these. If people ask in the comments to have an option without the Rauru arm (ie. with Link's original arm), I suppose I can do that.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The last significant change I made is that there's an option in the BNP for whether you want to stay true to &lt;i&gt;Tears of the Kingdom&lt;/i&gt; and not upgrade the Archaic Set, or if you want to be able to upgrade it.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;Oh, and note that long hair is not included. Sorry 'bout that. Other mods exist for that, though, no need to reinvent the wheel.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Many thanks to KB0MB for teaching me how to merge the arm on and allowing me to post this.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If there's any issues, just let me know in the comments and I'll take a look.</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/archaic_set_b4c23.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/archaic_set_26ab8.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Armor</category>
      <category>Skins</category>
    </item>
